Procs

proc match(buf: openArray[byte]): FileType {...}{.raises: [], tags: [].}
Returns a file type from matched magic number. Returns a empty FileType if buf was not matched any matchers.

Example:

var buf: seq[byte]
doAssert buf.match() == FileType()

from filetype/image import typeGif
doAssert @['G'.byte, 'I'.byte, 'F'.byte, '8'.byte, '7'.byte, 'a'.byte].match() == typeGif
proc matchFile(file: string): FileType {...}{.raises: [IOError, OSError, Exception],
    tags: [ReadDirEffect, ReadIOEffect, WriteIOEffect].}

Returns a file type from matched magic number. file is a file path.

Note: Not available for JS backend.
